# dataset (not the country-polygon fills used for WORLD_LANDMASS_PATH_D in
# world_map_path.py) — it excludes coastlines entirely, so overlaying it on the landmass
# silhouette adds only the political borders, not a second (redundant) coastline outline.
# Same equirectangular projection/viewBox as world_map_path.py for a 480x220 viewBox:
# x=(lon+180)/360*480, y=(90-lat)/180*220. Ramer-Douglas-Peucker decimated (epsilon=0.8px
# in projected space), segments with a projected bounding box under 3px on both axes
# dropped entirely (invisible at this scale, same threshold class as the landmass's
# dropped small islands). Regenerate by re-running the one-off script against a fresh
# ne_110m_admin_0_boundary_lines_land.geojson if a materially different projection/size
# is ever needed — not worth keeping the generator script in this repo for a static asset
# (same call as world_map_path.py).
